				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Rizlona's and Muse: What's the difference?<a name="36479"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 26 04 10:29 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm about to hit 65 and have noticed that Call of the Muse and Rizlona's Call of Flame both have the same description for the most part in the song listings
<br />

<br />
RCoF: Increase Spell Effectiveness by 15%; Increase Haste (Above Cap) by 30%; Restriction (Spell) - Hit Point spells only; Restriction (Spell) - Instant spells only; Restriction (Spell) - Detrimental spells only; Restriction (Target): Location based AE excluded; Restriction (Target): Point blank AE excluded; Restriction (Target): Targeted AE excluded; Restriction (Target): Giants excluded; Restriction (Target): Dragons excluded; Increase Limit: Max Level by 65; 
<br />

<br />
CotM: Increase Spell Effectiveness by 15%; Increase Haste (Above Cap) by 30%; Restriction (Spell) - Hit Point spells only; Increase Limit: Max Level by 65; Restriction (Spell) - Detrimental spells only; Restriction (Target): Location based AE excluded; Restriction (Target): Point blank AE excluded; Restriction (Target): Targeted AE excluded; Restriction (Target): Giants excluded; Restriction (Target): Dragons excluded; 
<br />

<br />

<br />
So what's the real difference and which would be better to my group, providing there is even a difference?
<br />
</span></td>
